gujarati.context:
Here are the translations:

The foolish one who has come is ignorant of the mouth of good knowledge; 
The wise one who has come, Ashtavakra, is an atheist, with a body like a dead tree branch, without a sound.

Here is the translation:

Avya Urvi Asuri, Bharadvaja Rishi ne Bhaguri;
Avya Rishi Angiraa Agasty, Satyadharma Shukra ne Samvarta.

The Gujarati couplet translates to:

"Came with a gaze like the eye of a snake, with a glance that pierced the heart; 
Parashar's words are bitter, like the honey of the Paila bee to the Bhrgu sage."

Not to Nathane vahala chho tapeeshvar, Prabhu sevaamaa chho tattapur;
Tame wali Narayna maani, kheeae ame fer nahi kaani.

Not to Nathane you are devoted, Oh God is your service truly yours; 
You have taken shelter of Narayana, we say there is no other way.
